<TITLE> Notorious Satkhira criminal killed in 'crossfire' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, Aug 19 (bdnews24.com)A regional leader of a faction of the extremist outfit Purbo Bangla Communist Party was killed in 'crossfire' on Wednesday when members of the police cornered him in central Satkhira. Police identified Lutfar Rahman Gazi, the leader of the Marxist-Leninist faction of the organisation, as the deceased, he was from Shahapur village in Tala upazila. "Lutfar was hit by a bullet at one stage of the shootout, after which his accomplices fled the scene," SM Kamruzzaman, officer-in-charge of Sadar Police Station, told bdnews24.com. Sub-inspector Ebad Ali and constables Aolad and Nazrul Islam were injured in the shootout, said Kamruzzaman. A locally manufactured handgun and three rounds of bullets were recovered from the spot. Lutfar Rahman Gazi stood accused in several murder cases, including that of former Tala upazila BNP leader Altaf Hossain and local fishermen association president Mirza Masud Hossain Jewel. He was also accused in multiple cases of robbery, extortion and forcibly taking control of land and water bodies. A large number of people from Lutfar's home district arrived at Satkhira Police Station on hearing news of his death. Kamruzzaman said deceased was declared dead at Satkhira Sadar Hospital shortly after the incident. bdnews24.com
